The paper deals with image captioning, which is a task related to computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The proposed method involves training a model with a self-retrieval module, which can be seen as a form of unsupervised learning (cs.LG). The approach also utilizes unlabeled images to boost performance, which is a common theme in machine learning (cs.AI). Finally, the paper involves evaluating the quality of generated captions, which can be seen as a form of information retrieval (cs.IR).
